                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-826">
                        <quote source="#bib826-1">Commonly known as Yoḥannan Saba (‘Elder’). An E.-Syr. monk, author of a Syriac
            collection of mystical discourses, letters, and maxims (‘chapters of
            knowledge’).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="description">In hagiography: John of Dalyatha was a famous spiritual author also called John Saba. He was a monk of the monastery of Mar Yozadaq in Qardu. His writings were condemned under the Synod of Timothy I, but they were rehabilitated by Isho bar Nun.</note>
